questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a financial transaction is sporadically not persisting to the database. A developer implemented the following logic within a Spring service to handle payment asynchronously:

java
@Service
public class PaymentService {
    @Autowired private PaymentRepository repo;

    @Transactional
    public void processPayment(Payment p) {
        CompletableFuture.runAsync(() -> {
            repo.save(p);
        });
    }
}

You are debugging a production issue where an API orchestrating multiple downstream microservices via `CompletableFuture.allOf()` occasionally hangs indefinitely or fails to return errors to the client when one of the downstream tasks encounters an exception:

java
public CompletableFuture<Response> orchestrate() {
    CompletableFuture<String> callA = CompletableFuture.supplyAsync(() -> serviceA.call());
    CompletableFuture<String> callB = CompletableFuture.supplyAsync(() -> serviceB.call());

    return CompletableFuture.allOf(callA, callB)
        .thenApply(v -> {
            String resA = callA.join();
            String resB = callB.join();
            return new Response(resA, resB);
        });
}
